Description: A small business connection network.
Full Description: AboutOurWork is a small business connection network that uses a data-driven approach to B2B networking. We're the Match.com for small businesses. Thousands of local networking events still take place daily and millions are spent to attend them. Every. Single. Day. Unfortunately, local networking events are a timesuck for small businesses and freelancers. Ask any small business owner and they'll tell you the same. They take a lot of time, take a lot of money, and key decision makers never attend events. And for the knowledge worker that can transact business globally, the local networking event offers little value. Finding the right leads at networking events is like trying to catch lightning in a bottle. AboutOurWork uses data to make the right B2B connections at the right time between their small business members at the right time so they can do more deals. Together.

Description: Crypto Key Stack is a software based hardware wallets help protect your keys while transacting.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Crypto Key Stack is a software based hardware wallets help protect your keys while transacting. Crypto Key Stack LLC was co-founded by Chris Gonyo and NFL veteran Israel Idonije in an effort to reduce the billions of dollars lost due to improper private key storage. The number of assets being stored and tracked on the blockchain is growing at an exponential rate, and they are all being secured by private keys. Realizing that software-based hardware wallets are excellent for cybersecurity,  but become vulnerable in the event of a physical disaster, Chris and Israel designed Crypto Key Stack to help preserve access to your assets in the event of a hardware failure and physical disaster. It was created out of a need for an affordable, high-quality stainless steel backup device that allowed users to store multiple cryptographic keys permanently.
Industry Groups: Blockchain and Cryptocurrency, Consumer Goods, Financial Services, Other, Payments, Privacy and Security, Software

Description: Environmental Monitoring In The Cloud.
Full Description: O-P-S was founded to provide turn-key, cloud-based, environmental monitoring management solutions for agencies responsible for testing samples against mandated requirements, yet often don’t have the resources to maintain compliance with the complex regulations from the EPA and states, and are subsequently causing thousands of violations every year ($112m calculated). Our mission is to provide solutions to support the management of public infrastructure systems (Water, Waste, Air, and Land quality) to improve national safety. For example in the United States alone there are 155,000 public drinking water systems that supply water to 320 million people.  In 2011 (latest data), those suppliers were reported to have made 196,110 violations of the EPA regulations in regards to the Clean Water and Clean Drinking Water Act.  OPS is designing WaterOPS to manage the complex task of meeting regulatory requirements in harmony with daily operations.  Our approach is one of integrating all levels of system operations from field inspectors, laboratories, and management through an intuitive program breaking down complicated regulations into manageable daily tasks.  This scalable solution is capable of managing the operational needs for:- -Monitoring & recording hundreds of thousands of samples per day -Assimilating data into alerts and reports to rapidly inform key personnel -Provide information on trends and advisory notices -Even predict violations before they happen The core engine of our solution is being designed to support the entire USA water system network of drinking water providers, with a particular focus on providing an affordable service for the vast majority of system operators (143,000) that are still using outmoded paper based logging (over 60% in a recent market survey).  It will then be used to manage other crucial environmental monitoring systems impacting public safety, such as solid/water/hazardous waste, air quality, and land/agricultural/farm monitoring. Not only this, OPS is building a geo-referenced knowledgebase to help municipalities deal with the encroaching issue that 70% of Water Operators are now only within 5-7 years of retirement and have few resources to transfer that knowledge into a format for the next generation. We believe the solutions under development will even have worldwide advantages in supporting environmental monitoring in developing countries due to its cost-effectiveness.
Founders: Charles Rowe, Evan Chou, Lee Beauchamp, Matt Beard, Tim Gantzhorn
